Here is a simple CSS code to style a button with a bright green background and white text:
```
.button {
  background-color: #34C759; /* bright green */
  color: #FFFFFF; /* white */
  padding: 10px 20px;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 5px;
  cursor: pointer;
}

.button:hover {
  background-color: #2ECC40; /* darker green on hover */
}
```
You can apply this CSS code to a button element in your HTML file by adding the class `button` to the button element, like this:
```
<button class="button">Click me!</button>
```
This will give your button a bright green background, white text, and a rounded corner. When you hover over the button, the background color will change to a darker green.

You can adjust the values of the CSS properties to customize the appearance of the button to your liking. For example, you can change the background color, text color, padding, border radius, and more.

